title: ICE when attempting to document `associated_const_equality`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(associated_const_equality)] pub enum ParseMode { Raw, } pub trait Parse { const PARSE_MODE: ParseMode; } pub trait RenderRaw: Parse {} ``` or ```Rust #![feature(associated_const_equality)] pub enum ParseMode { Raw, } pub trait Parse { const PARSE_MODE: ParseMode; } pub trait RenderRaw {} impl> RenderRaw for T {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.0-nightly (0468a00ae 2022-12-17) binary: rustc commit-hash: 0468a00ae3fd6ef1a6a0f9eaf637d7aa9e604acc commit-date: 2022-12-17 host: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'not yet implemented', src\librustdoc\html\format.rs:1660:18 error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.68.0-nightly (0468a00ae 2022-12-17) running on x86_64-pc-windows-msvc note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: end of query stack error: could not document `test-ice` ```
